						<summary>

						<p>This is another damaged record found in the same place. It is dated in the 4th year probably of the same king, and registers a grant of 15 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for a perpetual lamp in the temple, made by a donor whose name is lost. The amount is stated to have been invested with the <hi rend="italic">Ūrār</hi> of Kaitaṇḍalam in Dāmar-nāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
